  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nI use yarn workspaces and each package's `node_modules` is located in root directory, not in the package directory.\r\n\r\nWhen trying to run `truffle compile` in a package directory with using openzeppelin-solidity, truffle cannot resolve the path of `node_modules/openzeppelin-solidity` because it searches wrong directory.\r\n\r\n[Findup](https://www.npmjs.com/package/findup)-like behavior may fix it.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nUse yarn workspaces. It may seem like\r\n```\r\n/root\r\n└─node_modules\r\n       └─ openzeppelin-solidity\r\n└─packages\r\n        └─ sampleProject # using openzeppelin-solidity\r\n               └─ node_modules\r\n ```\r\n\r\nand run\r\n```bash\r\n$ truffle compile\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\ncompiled without errors\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\ncannot resolve openzeppelin-solidity\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: maxosX\r\n\r\n```\r\nTruffle v4.1.11 (core: 4.1.11)\r\nSolidity v0.4.24 (solc-js)\r\n\r\nnode.js v8.11.1\r\nnpm 5.6.0\r\n```",
